<p><b>Individual strengths</b><sup id=3D"cite_ref-potential-ivs_1-0" class=
=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Individua=
l_values#cite_note-potential-ivs-1"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>1<=
span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-official-=
individual-strengths_2-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://bulbapedia=
.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Individual_values#cite_note-official-individual-stren=
gths-2"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>2<span class=3D"cite-bracket">=
]</span></a></sup> (Japanese: <b><span lang=3D"ja" style=3D"margin: 0px;"><=
span class=3D"explain" title=3D"=E3=81=86=E3=81=BE=E3=82=8C=E3=81=A4=E3=81=
=8D=E3=81=AE=E3=81=A4=E3=82=88=E3=81=95">=E7=94=9F=E3=81=BE=E3=82=8C=E3=81=
=A4=E3=81=8D=E3=81=AE=E5=BC=B7=E3=81=95</span></span></b> <i>innate strengt=
hs</i>), commonly referred to by fans as <b>individual values</b> (Japanese=
: <b><span lang=3D"ja" style=3D"margin: 0px;"><span class=3D"explain" title=
=3D"=E3=81=93=E3=81=9F=E3=81=84=E3=81=A1">=E5=80=8B=E4=BD=93=E5=80=A4</span=
></span></b> <i>individual values</i>) and abbreviated as <b>IVs</b>, are a=
n immutable set of numeric values that function as a Pok=C3=A9mon's equival=
ent to <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/genes" class=3D"extiw" titl=
e=3D"wp:genes">genes</a>. They are instrumental in determining the <a href=
=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Stat" title=3D"Stat">stats</a> =
of a Pok=C3=A9mon, being responsible for the large variation in stats among=
 untrained Pok=C3=A9mon of the same species. In the context of <a href=3D"h=
ttps://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Generation_I" title=3D"Generation I"=
>Generations I</a> and <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/G=
eneration_II" title=3D"Generation II">II</a>, which have a different IV sys=
tem, IVs are also referred to as <b>determinant values</b> (DVs).
</p><p>Each Pok=C3=A9mon has an IV associated with any of the six stats, wi=
th that IV coming into calculation alongside the Pok=C3=A9mon's <a href=3D"=
https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Base_stats" title=3D"Base stats">ba=
se stats</a>, <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Nature" ti=
tle=3D"Nature">Nature</a>, and <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.ne=
t/wiki/Effort_values" title=3D"Effort values">EVs</a> to determine the actu=
al stat number. A Pok=C3=A9mon's IVs are fixed (and persisted <a href=3D"ht=
tps://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Pok%C3%A9mon_data_structure" class=3D=
"mw-disambig" title=3D"Pok=C3=A9mon data structure">within its data structu=
re</a>) when it is <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Pseud=
orandom_number_generation" title=3D"Pseudorandom number generation">generat=
ed by the game</a> (i.e. when it is <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagard=
en.net/wiki/Wild_Pok%C3%A9mon" title=3D"Wild Pok=C3=A9mon">encountered in t=
he wild</a> or <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Gift_Pok%=
C3%A9mon" title=3D"Gift Pok=C3=A9mon">given to the player by an NPC</a>), a=
nd cannot be changed (although <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.ne=
t/wiki/Hyper_Training" title=3D"Hyper Training">Hyper Training</a> causes s=
tats to become values corresponding the maximum IVs).
</p><p>In-game, while the term <b>potential</b> is often used to allude to =
IVs (such as by the <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Stat=
s_judge" title=3D"Stats judge">stats judge</a>), the exact technical nature=
 of IVs appears to be intentionally hidden to the player. According to <a h=
ref=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Shigeru_Ohmori" title=3D"Shi=
geru Ohmori">Shigeru Ohmori</a>, this facilitates to think of Pok=C3=A9mon =
as "real, living creatures".<sup id=3D"cite_ref-wired-masuda-ohmori_3-0" cl=
ass=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Indivi=
dual_values#cite_note-wired-masuda-ohmori-3"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[=
</span>3<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
