<div id=3D"cls-video-container-GVPYOwFj" class=3D"adthrive" style=3D"min-he=
ight: 403.875px;"><div></div></div><h2><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"Ge=
neration_I_and_II">Generation I and II</span></h2>
<p>In Generation I and II, only four IVs are stored for each individual Pok=
=C3=A9mon: Attack, Defense, Speed, and Special. Each of these is used to de=
termine their associated stat, with the HP IV determined from the IVs store=
d for the other four. IVs range from 0-15 (in binary 0000-1111).
</p><p>The HP IV is calculated by taking the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedi=
a.org/wiki/least_significant_bit" class=3D"extiw" title=3D"wp:least signifi=
cant bit">least significant bit</a> (the final binary digit) of the Attack,=
 Defense, Speed, and Special IVs, then creating a binary string by placing =
them in that order. As such, a Pok=C3=A9mon with an odd-number Attack IV ha=
s 8 added to its HP IV, an odd-number Defense IV has 4 added, an odd-number=
 Speed IV has 2 added, and an odd-number Special IV has 1 added.
</p><p>In Generation II, due to the Special stat being split into Special A=
ttack and Special Defense, the Special IV is used for both Special Attack a=
nd Special Defense.
</p><p>In Generation II, several things aside from stats are also based on =
stats IVs. From <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Generati=
on_III" title=3D"Generation III">Generation III</a> onward, all of these ex=
cept the <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Type" title=3D"=
Type">type</a> and <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Power=
" title=3D"Power">power</a> of <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.ne=
t/wiki/Hidden_Power_(move)" title=3D"Hidden Power (move)">Hidden Power</a> =
are determined by other variables, such as the Pok=C3=A9mon's <a href=3D"ht=
tps://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Personality_value" title=3D"Personali=
ty value">personality value</a>.
</p><p>In Generation I, due to correlations between <a href=3D"https://bulb=
apedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Pseudorandom_number_generation" title=3D"Pseudo=
random number generation">pseudorandom numbers</a>, Pok=C3=A9mon encountere=
d in those games in <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Tall=
_grass" title=3D"Tall grass">tall grass</a>, in <a href=3D"https://bulbaped=
ia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Cave_tile" title=3D"Cave tile">caves</a>, or by <a =
href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Surf_(move)" title=3D"Surf =
(move)">surfing</a> on <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/W=
ater_tile" title=3D"Water tile">water</a> have a limited pool of possible s=
ets of IVs, with the exact pool of possible sets of IVs depending on the en=
counter rate of the location they were encountered. Most significantly, any=
 Pok=C3=A9mon encountered in any of these ways cannot be <a href=3D"https:/=
/bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Shiny_Pok%C3%A9mon" title=3D"Shiny Pok=C3=
=A9mon">Shiny</a>. Conversely, <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.ne=
t/wiki/Fishing" title=3D"Fishing">Fishing</a> encounters, <a href=3D"https:=
//bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Gift_Pok%C3%A9mon" title=3D"Gift Pok=C3=
=A9mon">gift Pok=C3=A9mon</a> (including from <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia=
.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Pok%C3%A9mon_Stadium" title=3D"Pok=C3=A9mon Stadium">=
Pok=C3=A9mon Stadium</a>), stationary Pok=C3=A9mon (such as <a href=3D"http=
s://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Snorlax_(Pok%C3%A9mon)" title=3D"Snorla=
x (Pok=C3=A9mon)">Snorlax</a> and <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden=
.net/wiki/Mewtwo_(Pok%C3%A9mon)" title=3D"Mewtwo (Pok=C3=A9mon)">Mewtwo</a>=
), and <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/In-game_trade" ti=
tle=3D"In-game trade">in-game trades</a> can have any set of IVs.<sup id=3D=
"cite_ref-pokemonspeedruns_4-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://bulb=
apedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Individual_values#cite_note-pokemonspeedruns-4"=
><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>4<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span=
></a></sup>
</p>
