tent adthrive-content-1 adthrive-ad-cls" style=3D"min-height: 250px;"></div=
><h4><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"Gender">Gender</span></h4>
<p>In Generation II, a Pok=C3=A9mon's <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbaga=
rden.net/wiki/Gender" title=3D"Gender">gender</a> is determined based solel=
y on its physical <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Stat#A=
ttack" title=3D"Stat">Attack</a> IV when compared to a <a href=3D"https://b=
ulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/List_of_Pok%C3%A9mon_by_gender_ratio" title=
=3D"List of Pok=C3=A9mon by gender ratio">gender ratio</a>. A Pok=C3=A9mon =
is female if its physical Attack IV is less than or equal to its species' g=
ender ratio, otherwise it is male. For species that are exclusively one gen=
der or have no gender, the calculation based on the Attack IV is ignored.
</p><p>Due to this calculation, it is impossible to obtain a female Pok=C3=
=A9mon with high physical Attack, unless the Pok=C3=A9mon is a member of an=
 all-female species like <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki=
/Jynx_(Pok%C3%A9mon)" title=3D"Jynx (Pok=C3=A9mon)">Jynx</a> or <a href=3D"=
https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Chansey_(Pok%C3%A9mon)" title=3D"Ch=
ansey (Pok=C3=A9mon)">Chansey</a>. First partner Pok=C3=A9mon and others wi=
th a gender ratio of seven males to one female are the most affected, with =
the maximum physical Attack IV for a female Pok=C3=A9mon of those species b=
eing 1.
</p>
