><h4><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"Shininess">Shininess</span></h4>
<p>In Generation II, whether or not a Pok=C3=A9mon is Shiny is determined b=
y its IVs.
</p><p>A Pok=C3=A9mon is Shiny if and only if both of the following conditi=
ons are met
</p>
<ul><li>Its Defense, Speed, and Special IVs are all 10.</li>
<li>Its Attack IV is 2, 3, 6, 7, 10, 11, 14, or 15.</li></ul>
<p>Normally, when the player encounters a Pok=C3=A9mon in the wild or recei=
ves a Pok=C3=A9mon as a gift in Generation II, all possible sets of IVs hav=
e an equal probability. Since there are 8 possible sets of IVs for Shiny Po=
k=C3=A9mon of the 65,536 distinct sets of IVs, there is a 1/8192 chance of =
a Pok=C3=A9mon being Shiny when its IVs are selected at random. This is the=
 same probability of a wild Pok=C3=A9mon being Shiny in Generation III, IV,=
 and V.
</p><p>Due to correlations between <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarde=
n.net/wiki/Pseudorandom_number_generation" title=3D"Pseudorandom number gen=
eration">pseudorandom numbers</a> in the Generation I games, Pok=C3=A9mon e=
ncountered in those games in <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/=
wiki/Tall_grass" title=3D"Tall grass">tall grass</a>, in <a href=3D"https:/=
/bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Cave_tile" title=3D"Cave tile">caves</a>, =
or by <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Surf_(move)" title=
=3D"Surf (move)">surfing</a> on <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.n=
et/wiki/Water_tile" title=3D"Water tile">water</a> cannot have a set of IVs=
 that would allow them to be Shiny in Generation II. <a href=3D"https://bul=
bapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Fishing" title=3D"Fishing">Fishing</a> encount=
ers, <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Gift_Pok%C3%A9mon" =
title=3D"Gift Pok=C3=A9mon">gift Pok=C3=A9mon</a> (including from <a href=
=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Pok%C3%A9mon_Stadium" title=3D"=
Pok=C3=A9mon Stadium">Pok=C3=A9mon Stadium</a>), stationary Pok=C3=A9mon (s=
uch as <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Snorlax_(Pok%C3%A=
9mon)" title=3D"Snorlax (Pok=C3=A9mon)">Snorlax</a> and <a href=3D"https://=
bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Mewtwo_(Pok%C3%A9mon)" title=3D"Mewtwo (Pok=
=C3=A9mon)">Mewtwo</a>), and <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/=
wiki/In-game_trade" title=3D"In-game trade">in-game trades</a> can have any=
 set of IVs, so they always have the same 1/8192 chance of having a Shiny I=
V combination.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-pokemonspeedruns_4-1" class=3D"reference"=
><a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Individual_values#cite_=
note-pokemonspeedruns-4"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>4<span class=
=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p>The <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Red_Gyarados"=
 title=3D"Red Gyarados">Red Gyarados</a> at the <a href=3D"https://bulbaped=
ia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Lake_of_Rage" title=3D"Lake of Rage">Lake of Rage</=
a>, which is guaranteed to be Shiny, has predetermined IVs, with an Attack =
IV of 14 and all other stats being 10, except HP which is 0. When <a href=
=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Pok%C3%A9mon_breeding" title=3D=
"Pok=C3=A9mon breeding">breeding</a> Pok=C3=A9mon, because IVs are inherite=
d from the Pok=C3=A9mon's parents, the probability of the bred Pok=C3=A9mon=
 being Shiny is highly dependent on the parents' IVs.
</p><p>Due to HP IV being calculated from the other IVs, a Shiny Pok=C3=A9m=
on's HP IV can only be 0 (if the Attack IV is even) or 8 (if the Attack IV =
is odd). Since 0 and 1 are not possible Attack IVs for a Shiny Pok=C3=A9mon=
, female Pok=C3=A9mon of <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki=
/Category:Pok%C3%A9mon_with_a_gender_ratio_of_seven_males_to_one_female" ti=
tle=3D"Category:Pok=C3=A9mon with a gender ratio of seven males to one fema=
le">species with a seven male to one female ratio</a> can never be Shiny in=
 Generation II.
</p>
<dl><dt>Example</dt></dl>
<p>For two <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Sandshrew_(Po=
k%C3%A9mon)" title=3D"Sandshrew (Pok=C3=A9mon)">Sandshrew</a> caught in <a =
href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Union_Cave" title=3D"Union =
Cave">Union Cave</a> (Sandshrew A is Shiny, Sandshrew B is not Shiny):
</p>
