><h4><span id=3D"Unown.27s_letter"></span><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D=
"Unown's_letter">Unown's letter</span></h4>
<p>In Generation II, <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Uno=
wn_(Pok%C3%A9mon)" title=3D"Unown (Pok=C3=A9mon)">Unown</a>'s letter is tak=
en from the combination of the center two bits of the Attack, Defense, Spee=
d and Special IV <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/nibble" class=3D"=
extiw" title=3D"wp:nibble">nibbles</a>. This combination is then divided by=
 ten, and the result is <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Floor_func=
tion" class=3D"extiw" title=3D"wp:Floor function">rounded down (<i>floor[]<=
/i>)</a> to only include the integer part of the number. This integer will =
range from 0-25, corresponding to a letter in the <a href=3D"https://en.wik=
ipedia.org/wiki/Latin_alphabet" class=3D"extiw" title=3D"wp:Latin alphabet"=
>Latin alphabet</a>, which will be the Unown's letter (where 0=3DA, 1=3DB, =
2=3DC, ..., 23=3DX, 24=3DY, 25=3DZ).
</p><p>In Generation II, due to this method of calculating Unown's letter a=
nd the way that <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Shiny_Po=
k%C3%A9mon" title=3D"Shiny Pok=C3=A9mon">Shiny</a> Pok=C3=A9mon are determi=
ned, a Shiny Unown can only exist in the shape of the letter I or V. Additi=
onally, due to this method of calculating Unown's letter, only 6 combinatio=
ns correspond to Unown Z, whereas 10 combinations correspond to every other=
 Unown, making Unown Z less common.
</p><p>In Generation III, Unown's letter is determined by the Pok=C3=A9mon'=
s <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Personality_value" tit=
le=3D"Personality value">personality value</a>. From Generation IV onward, =
it is determined by a separate form identifier. Generation III also introdu=
ced Unown '!' or '?'.
</p>
