><h4><span id=3D"Magikarp.27s_size"></span><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=
=3D"Magikarp's_size">Magikarp's size</span></h4>
<dl><dd><i>Main article: <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki=
/Size_and_weight_variation#Generation_II" title=3D"Size and weight variatio=
n">Size and weight variation =E2=86=92 Generation II</a></i></dd></dl>
<p>At the <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Lake_of_Rage" =
title=3D"Lake of Rage">Lake of Rage</a>, there is a <a href=3D"https://bulb=
apedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Fishing_Brothers#Lake_of_Rage_Fishing_Guru" tit=
le=3D"Fishing Brothers">Fishing Guru</a> who requests to see large Magikarp=
 after the player defeats <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wik=
i/Team_Rocket" title=3D"Team Rocket">Team Rocket</a> at <a href=3D"https://=
bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Team_Rocket_HQ" title=3D"Team Rocket HQ">th=
eir hideout</a> in <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Mahog=
any_Town" title=3D"Mahogany Town">Mahogany Town</a>. If the Fishing Guru is=
 shown a Magikarp bigger than the previous record, he gives the player a pr=
ize.
</p><p>The size of Magikarp is calculated from its IVs and its <a href=3D"h=
ttps://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Original_Trainer" title=3D"Original =
Trainer">Original Trainer</a>'s <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.n=
et/wiki/Trainer_ID_number" title=3D"Trainer ID number">Trainer ID number</a=
>. Sizes were intended to follow a <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki=
/normal_distribution" class=3D"extiw" title=3D"wp:normal distribution">norm=
al distribution</a>, but due to various bugs and oversights in the code, th=
e sizes only roughly follow it.
</p><p>In some circumstances, when encountering a wild Magikarp, the game c=
an regenerate its IVs once in order to try to make it smaller or larger. In=
 the non-English versions, Magikarp initially bigger than 160&nbsp;cm may h=
ave their IVs regenerated, in an effort to make large Magikarp more rare; i=
n the English versions, this fails to occur at all due to a unit conversion=
 error. Magikarp caught in the Lake of Rage were intended to be larger on a=
verage than Magikarp caught elsewhere, by regenerating the IVs of wild Magi=
karp that are initially 4'0" (122.0 cm) or smaller in English games, or 102=
.4 cm (3'4") or smaller in non-English games, 60% of the time; due to a pro=
gramming error, all wild Magikarp that meet the threshold have their IVs re=
generated this way except for those in the Lake of Rage and <a href=3D"http=
s://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Route" title=3D"Route">Routes</a> <a hr=
ef=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Kanto_Route_20" title=3D"Kant=
o Route 20">20</a>, <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Joht=
o_Route_43" title=3D"Johto Route 43">43</a>, and <a href=3D"https://bulbape=
dia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Johto_Route_44" title=3D"Johto Route 44">44</a>.
</p>
<div id=3D"AdThrive_Content_5_tablet" class=3D"adthrive-ad adthrive-content=
 adthrive-content-5 adthrive-ad-cls" style=3D"min-height: 250px;"></div><h4=
><span id=3D"Smeargle.27s_patterns.27_colors"></span><span class=3D"mw-head=
line" id=3D"Smeargle's_patterns'_colors">Smeargle's patterns' colors</span>=
</h4>
<p>In <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Pok%C3%A9mon_Stadi=
um_2" title=3D"Pok=C3=A9mon Stadium 2">Pok=C3=A9mon Stadium 2</a>, the patt=
erns on <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Smeargle_(Pok%C3=
%A9mon)" title=3D"Smeargle (Pok=C3=A9mon)">Smeargle</a>'s back and tail can=
 be red, green or blue depending on its IVs.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-5" class=3D=
"reference"><a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Individual_v=
alues#cite_note-5"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>5<span class=3D"cit=
e-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p>The games takes the Special, Defense, Speed and Attack values in tha=
t order, and makes them the digits of a 4-digit hexadecimal number. The col=
ors are determined from the result of <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w=
iki/modulo_operation" class=3D"extiw" title=3D"wp:modulo operation">modulo<=
/a> 9 on that number. The colors are cycled through in order of red, green =
and blue, with the back pattern changing every 3; that is 0-2 will give the=
 same color for back pattern but different colors for the tail pattern.
</p><p>The colors are affected by Shininess; due to the fact that both the =
pattern colors and Shininess is determined by IVs, a Shiny Smeargle will on=
ly have pattern ID of 2, 3, 4, 6, 7 or 8.
</p>
<dl><dt>Example</dt></dl>
