><h4><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"Hidden_Power">Hidden Power</span></h=
4>
<dl><dd><i>Main article: <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki=
/Hidden_Power_(move)/Calculation" title=3D"Hidden Power (move)/Calculation"=
>Hidden Power (move)/Calculation</a></i></dd></dl>
<p>The calculated <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Type" =
title=3D"Type">Type</a> and <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/w=
iki/Power" title=3D"Power">Power</a> of the move <a href=3D"https://bulbape=
dia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Hidden_Power_(move)" title=3D"Hidden Power (move)"=
>Hidden Power</a> is based on the IVs of the Pok=C3=A9mon. Hidden Power can=
 be of any type aside from <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wi=
ki/Normal_(type)" title=3D"Normal (type)">Normal</a>, and can have a power =
between 31 and 70. The formula used in Generation II is different to the on=
e used in later generations.
</p><p>The move's type is determined by the two <a href=3D"https://en.wikip=
edia.org/wiki/least_significant_bit" class=3D"extiw" title=3D"wp:least sign=
ificant bit">least significant bits</a> of the Attack and Defense IVs. The =
move's power is determined by the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/=
most_significant_bit" class=3D"extiw" title=3D"wp:most significant bit">mos=
t significant bit</a> of each of the Pok=C3=A9mon's IVs, as well as the two=
 least significant bits of the Special IVs.
</p>
<h4><span id=3D"NPC.27s_Pok.C3.A9mon"></span><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=
=3D"NPC's_Pok=C3=A9mon">NPC's Pok=C3=A9mon</span></h4>
<ul><li>In <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Generation_I"=
 title=3D"Generation I">Generation I</a>, all NPC's Pok=C3=A9mon have the s=
ame DVs:
<ul><li>Attack =3D 9</li>
<li>Defense, Special, Speed =3D 8</li></ul></li>
<li>In <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Generation_II" ti=
tle=3D"Generation II">Generation II</a>, all Pok=C3=A9mon owned by the same=
 NPC share the same DVs.
<ul><li>See <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/List_of_NPC%=
27s_Pok%C3%A9mon%27s_DVs_in_Generation_II" title=3D"List of NPC's Pok=C3=A9=
mon's DVs in Generation II">List of NPC's Pok=C3=A9mon's DVs in Generation =
II</a></li></ul></li></ul>
<div id=3D"AdThrive_Content_7_tablet" class=3D"adthrive-ad adthrive-content=
 adthrive-content-7 adthrive-ad-cls" style=3D"min-height: 250px;"></div><h2=
><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"Generation_III_onward">Generation III on=
ward</span></h2>
<p>In Generation III, the IV system was completely overhauled; now, IVs ran=
ge from 0-31 rather than 0-15, with HP and Special Defense getting their ow=
n independent IVs.
</p><p>Since IVs now have twice the range, they now have half the influence=
 on a Pok=C3=A9mon's stats. The <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.n=
et/wiki/Effort_values" title=3D"Effort values">EV</a> system overhaul and t=
he addition of <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Nature" t=
itle=3D"Nature">Natures</a> also result in small changes to formula used to=
 determine stats. The <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Pe=
rsonality_value" title=3D"Personality value">personality value</a> was intr=
oduced in Generation III, which handles a Pok=C3=A9mon's <a href=3D"https:/=
/bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Gender" title=3D"Gender">gender</a> and <a=
 href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Shiny_Pok%C3%A9mon" title=
=3D"Shiny Pok=C3=A9mon">Shiny status</a> instead, as well as several other =
properties; in Generation III, Unown's form was also handled using the pers=
onality value, but this is stored separately in Generation IV onward.
</p><p>The overhaul of the Pok=C3=A9mon data structure is one of the reason=
s why it was not made possible to trade between <a href=3D"https://bulbaped=
ia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Generation_II" title=3D"Generation II">Generation I=
I</a> and <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Generation_III=
" title=3D"Generation III">Generation III</a> games.
</p>
<h3><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"Usage_2">Usage</span></h3>
