</p><h4><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"Hidden_Power_2">Hidden Power</spa=
n></h4>
<dl><dd><i>Main article: <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki=
/Hidden_Power_(move)/Calculation" title=3D"Hidden Power (move)/Calculation"=
>Hidden Power (move)/Calculation</a></i></dd></dl>
<p>The calculated <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Type" =
title=3D"Type">Type</a> and <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/w=
iki/Power" title=3D"Power">Power</a> of the move <a href=3D"https://bulbape=
dia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Hidden_Power_(move)" title=3D"Hidden Power (move)"=
>Hidden Power</a> is based on the IVs of the Pok=C3=A9mon. Hidden Power can=
 be of any type aside from <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wi=
ki/Normal_(type)" title=3D"Normal (type)">Normal</a> and <a href=3D"https:/=
/bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Fairy_(type)" title=3D"Fairy (type)">Fairy=
</a>, and prior to <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Gener=
ation_VI" title=3D"Generation VI">Generation VI</a>, have a power between 3=
0 and 70.
</p><p>The least significant bit of each IV determines the move's Type, and=
 the second-least significant bit of each determines the move's Power.
</p>
<div id=3D"AdThrive_Content_9_tablet" class=3D"adthrive-ad adthrive-content=
 adthrive-content-9 adthrive-ad-cls" style=3D"min-height: 250px;"></div><h3=
><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"Evaluation">Evaluation</span></h3>
<h4><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"Stats_judge">Stats judge</span></h4>
<dl><dd><i>Main article: <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki=
/Stats_judge" title=3D"Stats judge">Stats judge</a></i></dd></dl>
<p>From <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Pok%C3%A9mon_Eme=
rald_Version" title=3D"Pok=C3=A9mon Emerald Version">Pok=C3=A9mon Emerald</=
a> onward, there is a stats judge in the game in the region's battle facili=
ty or the city it is in. They give qualitative evaluations of the Pok=C3=A9=
mon's IVs.
</p>
<ul><li>In <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Pok%C3%A9mon_=
Emerald_Version" title=3D"Pok=C3=A9mon Emerald Version">Pok=C3=A9mon Emeral=
d</a>, <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Stats_judge#In_Ge=
neration_III" title=3D"Stats judge">elderly man</a> in the house north of t=
he <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Battle_Frontier_(Gene=
ration_III)" title=3D"Battle Frontier (Generation III)">Battle Frontier</a>=
's <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Pok%C3%A9mon_Center" =
title=3D"Pok=C3=A9mon Center">Pok=C3=A9mon Center</a> will evaluate the Pok=
=C3=A9mon's IVs in a roundabout way.</li>
<li>In the <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Generation_IV=
" title=3D"Generation IV">Generation IV</a> games, a man in the <a href=3D"=
https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Battle_Tower_(Sinnoh)" title=3D"Bat=
tle Tower (Sinnoh)">Battle Tower</a> or <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulba=
garden.net/wiki/Battle_Frontier_(Generation_IV)" title=3D"Battle Frontier (=
Generation IV)">Battle Frontier</a> will evaluate the Pok=C3=A9mon's IVs in=
 a roundabout way.</li>
<li>In the <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Generation_V"=
 title=3D"Generation V">Generation V</a> games, an <a href=3D"https://bulba=
pedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Ace_Trainer_(Trainer_class)" title=3D"Ace Traine=
r (Trainer class)">Ace Trainer</a> in the <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bul=
bagarden.net/wiki/Battle_Subway#Gear_Station" title=3D"Battle Subway">Gear =
Station</a> will evaluate the Pok=C3=A9mon's IVs in a roundabout way, after=
 the player enters the <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/H=
all_of_Fame" title=3D"Hall of Fame">Hall of Fame</a>.</li>
<li>In <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Pok%C3%A9mon_X_an=
d_Y" title=3D"Pok=C3=A9mon X and Y">Pok=C3=A9mon X and Y</a>, an Ace Traine=
r in the <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Kiloude_City" t=
itle=3D"Kiloude City">Kiloude City</a> <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbag=
arden.net/wiki/Pok%C3%A9mon_Center" title=3D"Pok=C3=A9mon Center">Pok=C3=A9=
mon Center</a> will evaluate the Pok=C3=A9mon's IVs in a roundabout way.</l=
i>
<li>In <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Pok%C3%A9mon_Omeg=
a_Ruby_and_Alpha_Sapphire" title=3D"Pok=C3=A9mon Omega Ruby and Alpha Sapph=
ire">Pok=C3=A9mon Omega Ruby and Alpha Sapphire</a>, an Ace Trainer in the =
<a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Battle_Resort" title=3D"=
Battle Resort">Battle Resort</a> <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.=
net/wiki/Pok%C3%A9mon_Center" title=3D"Pok=C3=A9mon Center">Pok=C3=A9mon Ce=
nter</a> will evaluate the Pok=C3=A9mon's IVs in a roundabout way.</li>
<li>In <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Pok%C3%A9mon_Sun_=
and_Moon" title=3D"Pok=C3=A9mon Sun and Moon">Pok=C3=A9mon Sun and Moon</a>=
, if the player has hatched 20 <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.ne=
t/wiki/Pok%C3%A9mon_Eggs" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Pok=C3=A9mon Eggs"=
>Eggs</a>, an Ace Trainer standing by the <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bul=
bagarden.net/wiki/Battle_Tree" title=3D"Battle Tree">Battle Tree</a> recept=
ionist will upgrade the <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/=
Pok%C3%A9mon_Storage_System" title=3D"Pok=C3=A9mon Storage System">Pok=C3=
=A9mon Storage System</a> with the Judge program. The Judge program will sh=
ow a graph of how IVs are placed and a comment on the overall numbers.</li>=
</ul>
<p>Starting in Generation VI, the stats judge will also specifically note 0=
 IVs.
</p><p>Starting in Generation VII, players can view a Pok=C3=A9mon's IVs di=
rectly using the Judge Function.
</p>
