h4><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"Camera_view">Camera view</span></h4>
<p>In <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Pok%C3%A9mon_Brill=
iant_Diamond_and_Shining_Pearl" title=3D"Pok=C3=A9mon Brilliant Diamond and=
 Shining Pearl">Pok=C3=A9mon Brilliant Diamond and Shining Pearl</a>, if a =
<a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Wild_Pok%C3%A9mon" title=
=3D"Wild Pok=C3=A9mon">wild Pok=C3=A9mon</a> has two or more IVs of 31, the=
 camera view shows the <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/P=
layer_character" title=3D"Player character">player</a> first.
</p>
<h3><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"Influence">Influence</span></h3>
<p>Beginning in <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Generati=
on_II" title=3D"Generation II">Generation II</a>, <a href=3D"https://bulbap=
edia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/In-game_trade" title=3D"In-game trade">in-game tr=
ades</a> in many games involve the received Pok=C3=A9mon having fixed IVs. =
This usually manifests either as a fixed set of IVs across all stats, or mo=
stly random IVs mixed with select IVs fixed at maximum value.
</p><p>The <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Red_Gyarados"=
 title=3D"Red Gyarados">Red Gyarados</a> encountered in <a href=3D"https://=
bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Pok%C3%A9mon_Gold_and_Silver_Versions" titl=
e=3D"Pok=C3=A9mon Gold and Silver Versions">Pok=C3=A9mon Gold, Silver</a>, =
and <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Pok%C3%A9mon_Crystal=
_Version" title=3D"Pok=C3=A9mon Crystal Version">Crystal</a> has a set of f=
ixed individual values, partly as a consequence of the implementation of <a=
 href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Shiny_Pok%C3%A9mon" title=
=3D"Shiny Pok=C3=A9mon">Shiny Pok=C3=A9mon</a> in these games. This trait g=
uarantees that it will always be Shiny.
</p><p>In <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Pok%C3%A9mon_H=
eartGold_and_SoulSilver_Versions" title=3D"Pok=C3=A9mon HeartGold and SoulS=
ilver Versions">Pok=C3=A9mon HeartGold and SoulSilver</a>, all Pok=C3=A9mon=
 encountered in the <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Safa=
ri_Zone_(Johto)" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Safari Zone (Johto)">Safari=
 Zone</a> and during the <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki=
/Bug_Catching_Contest" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Bug Catching Contest"=
>Bug Catching Contest</a> will have their IVs rerolled up to 4 times if non=
e of the generated IVs are 31.
</p><p>In <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Pok%C3%A9mon_X=
_and_Y" title=3D"Pok=C3=A9mon X and Y">Pok=C3=A9mon X and Y</a>, all Pok=C3=
=A9mon in the <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/No_Eggs_Di=
scovered_(Egg_Group)" title=3D"No Eggs Discovered (Egg Group)">No Eggs Disc=
overed Egg Group</a> are guaranteed to have at least three IVs of 31 when e=
ncountered in the wild or obtained as a gift (except via <a href=3D"https:/=
/bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Mystery_Gift" title=3D"Mystery Gift">Myste=
ry Gift</a>). In <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Pok%C3%=
A9mon_Omega_Ruby_and_Alpha_Sapphire" title=3D"Pok=C3=A9mon Omega Ruby and A=
lpha Sapphire">Pok=C3=A9mon Omega Ruby and Alpha Sapphire</a>, this only ap=
plies to <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Legendary_Pok%C=
3%A9mon" title=3D"Legendary Pok=C3=A9mon">Legendary</a> and <a href=3D"http=
s://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Mythical_Pok%C3%A9mon" title=3D"Mythica=
l Pok=C3=A9mon">Mythical Pok=C3=A9mon</a>. Starting in <a href=3D"https://b=
ulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Generation_VII" title=3D"Generation VII">Gen=
eration VII</a>, this applies to Legendary Pok=C3=A9mon, Mythical Pok=C3=A9=
mon, and <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Ultra_Beast" ti=
tle=3D"Ultra Beast">Ultra Beasts</a>.
</p><p>In Pok=C3=A9mon X and Y, all Pok=C3=A9mon encountered in the <a href=
=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Friend_Safari" title=3D"Friend =
Safari">Friend Safari</a> are guaranteed to have at least two IVs of 31. In=
 Pok=C3=A9mon Omega Ruby and Alpha Sapphire, <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.=
bulbagarden.net/wiki/DexNav#Hidden_Pok%C3%A9mon" title=3D"DexNav">hidden Po=
k=C3=A9mon</a> can have up to three IVs guaranteed to be 31.
</p><p>In <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Pok%C3%A9mon_S=
un_and_Moon" title=3D"Pok=C3=A9mon Sun and Moon">Pok=C3=A9mon Sun and Moon<=
/a>, ally Pok=C3=A9mon called in <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.=
net/wiki/SOS_Battle" title=3D"SOS Battle">SOS Battles</a> will begin to hav=
e increasing numbers of guaranteed perfect IVs as the chain of allies calle=
d continues to build (up to a minimum of four once the chain is at 30 or hi=
gher). Additionally, starting in these games, <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia=
.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Hyper_Training" title=3D"Hyper Training">Hyper Traini=
ng</a> allows the player to make a Pok=C3=A9mon's stats act as if the Pok=
=C3=A9mon had maximum IVs. However, this does not actually change the IVs, =
so its true IVs are still used for the purposes of <a href=3D"https://bulba=
pedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Hidden_Power_(move)" title=3D"Hidden Power (move=
)">Hidden Power</a> and <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/=
Pok%C3%A9mon_breeding" title=3D"Pok=C3=A9mon breeding">breeding</a>.
</p><p>In <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Pok%C3%A9mon_L=
et%27s_Go,_Pikachu!_and_Let%27s_Go,_Eevee!" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"=
Pok=C3=A9mon Let's Go, Pikachu! and Let's Go, Eevee!">Pok=C3=A9mon Let's Go=
, Pikachu! and Let's Go, Eevee!</a>, the <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulb=
agarden.net/wiki/Partner_Pok%C3%A9mon_(Let%27s_Go,_Pikachu!_and_Let%27s_Go,=
_Eevee!)" title=3D"Partner Pok=C3=A9mon (Let's Go, Pikachu! and Let's Go, E=
evee!)">partner</a> <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Pika=
chu_(Pok%C3%A9mon)" title=3D"Pikachu (Pok=C3=A9mon)">Pikachu</a> and partne=
r <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Eevee_(Pok%C3%A9mon)" =
title=3D"Eevee (Pok=C3=A9mon)">Eevee</a> are always guaranteed a perfect 31=
 in all IVs. Additionally, Pok=C3=A9mon encountered as part of a <a href=3D=
"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Catch_Combo" title=3D"Catch Combo"=
>Catch Combo</a> chain will begin to have increasing numbers of guaranteed =
perfect IVs as the chain continues to build (up to a minimum of four once t=
he chain is at 31 or higher).
</p><p>In <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Pok%C3%A9mon_B=
rilliant_Diamond_and_Shining_Pearl" title=3D"Pok=C3=A9mon Brilliant Diamond=
 and Shining Pearl">Pok=C3=A9mon Brilliant Diamond and Shining Pearl</a>, t=
he <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Pok%C3%A9_Radar#Chain=
_Bonuses" title=3D"Pok=C3=A9 Radar">Pok=C3=A9 Radar</a> will force Pok=C3=
=A9mon encountered at specific chain lengths to have increasing amounts of =
perfect IVs.
</p><p>In <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Pok%C3%A9mon_L=
egends:_Arceus" title=3D"Pok=C3=A9mon Legends: Arceus">Pok=C3=A9mon Legends=
: Arceus</a>, all <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Alpha_=
Pok%C3%A9mon" title=3D"Alpha Pok=C3=A9mon">alpha</a> Pok=C3=A9mon are guara=
nteed to have a perfect 31 in at least three of their IVs. Additionally, al=
l Pok=C3=A9mon found in the second wave of an individual outbreak within a =
<a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Mass_outbreak#Pok%C3%A9m=
on_Legends:_Arceus" title=3D"Mass outbreak">massive mass outbreak</a> will =
have at least three perfect 31 IVs, whether alpha or not.
</p><p>In <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Pok%C3%A9mon_S=
carlet_and_Violet" title=3D"Pok=C3=A9mon Scarlet and Violet">Pok=C3=A9mon S=
carlet and Violet</a>, Pok=C3=A9mon encountered in <a href=3D"https://bulba=
pedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Tera_Raid_Battle" title=3D"Tera Raid Battle">Ter=
a Raid Battles</a> are guaranteed to have perfect 31 in their IVs. They hav=
e one guaranteed perfect IV in one- and two-star raids, and then one extra =
for each star beyond the first two. The IVs of the former <a href=3D"https:=
//bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Titan_Pok%C3%A9mon" title=3D"Titan Pok=C3=
=A9mon">Titan Pok=C3=A9mon</a> are all fixed at 30 for all stats. <a href=
=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Gouging_Fire_(Pok%C3%A9mon)" ti=
tle=3D"Gouging Fire (Pok=C3=A9mon)">Gouging Fire</a>, <a href=3D"https://bu=
lbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Raging_Bolt_(Pok%C3%A9mon)" title=3D"Raging B=
olt (Pok=C3=A9mon)">Raging Bolt</a>, <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagar=
den.net/wiki/Iron_Crown_(Pok%C3%A9mon)" title=3D"Iron Crown (Pok=C3=A9mon)"=
>Iron Crown</a> and <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Iron=
_Boulder_(Pok%C3%A9mon)" title=3D"Iron Boulder (Pok=C3=A9mon)">Iron Boulder=
</a> also have set IVs of 20 for all stats.
</p>
<div id=3D"AdThrive_Content_12_tablet" class=3D"adthrive-ad adthrive-conten=
t adthrive-content-12 adthrive-ad-cls" style=3D"min-height: 250px;"></div><=
h4><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"Breeding">Breeding</span></h4>
<dl><dd><i>Main article: <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki=
/Pok%C3%A9mon_breeding#Inheriting_stats" title=3D"Pok=C3=A9mon breeding">Po=
k=C3=A9mon breeding =E2=86=92 Inheriting stats</a></i></dd></dl>
<p>Starting in <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Pok%C3%A9=
mon_HeartGold_and_SoulSilver_Versions" title=3D"Pok=C3=A9mon HeartGold and =
SoulSilver Versions">Pok=C3=A9mon HeartGold and SoulSilver</a>, a parent ho=
lding a <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Power_item" titl=
e=3D"Power item">Power item</a> will pass the IV corresponding to the same =
stat to its children.
</p><p>Starting in <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Gener=
ation_VI" title=3D"Generation VI">Generation VI</a>, if either of a Pok=C3=
=A9mon's parents were holding a <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.n=
et/wiki/Destiny_Knot" title=3D"Destiny Knot">Destiny Knot</a>, the child wi=
ll inherit 5 of its 6 IVs from its parents.
</p>
<h3><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"Storage">Storage</span></h3>
<p>IVs are now all stored together as a single 32-bit value. Since IVs requ=
ire 30 bits to be stored, the two <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/=
most_significant_bit" class=3D"extiw" title=3D"wp:most significant bit">mos=
t significant bits</a> of this value are used to store other data.
</p><p>In Generation III, the most significant bit specifies which of two <=
a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Ability" title=3D"Ability=
">Abilities</a> a Pok=C3=A9mon has (if it has potential to have more than o=
ne). If the Pok=C3=A9mon's species can have only one Ability in Generation =
III, the Ability bit is forced to 0 by the game (if it is forced to be 1, "=
No ability" will be listed as the Pok=C3=A9mon's Ability).
</p><p>In Generation IV onward, the most significant bit instead specifies =
whether or not the Pok=C3=A9mon is <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarde=
n.net/wiki/Nickname" title=3D"Nickname">nicknamed</a>, while the second-mos=
t significant bit fulfills the same role as in Generation III. This allows =
an unnicknamed Pok=C3=A9mon traded to a game of a different language to ret=
ain its name in the language of the previous game, but still change its nam=
e upon <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Evolution" title=
=3D"Evolution">Evolution</a>.
</p><p>The second-most significant bit specifies whether or not the Pok=C3=
=A9mon is an unhatched <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/P=
ok%C3%A9mon_Egg" title=3D"Pok=C3=A9mon Egg">Egg</a> or not.
</p><p>The remaining 30 bits are the IVs, five bits apiece, in the order Sp=
. Def, Sp. Atk, Speed, Defense, Attack, and HP.
</p>
<h3><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"Conversion_from_other_systems">Conver=
sion from other systems</span></h3>
<h4><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"Generation_I_and_II_2">Generation I a=
nd II</span></h4>
<p>Pok=C3=A9mon can be transported from the Generation I and II core series=
 games to <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Pok%C3%A9mon_B=
ank" title=3D"Pok=C3=A9mon Bank">Pok=C3=A9mon Bank</a> using the <a href=3D=
"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Pok%C3%A9_Transporter" title=3D"Po=
k=C3=A9 Transporter">Pok=C3=A9 Transporter</a>. Due to these games having a=
 different IV system to later generations, the IVs of transported Pok=C3=A9=
mon are regenerated, but it is guaranteed to have at least three IVs of 31 =
(five if it is <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Mythical_=
Pok%C3%A9mon" title=3D"Mythical Pok=C3=A9mon">Mythical</a>). There is no re=
lationship between the Pok=C3=A9mon's IVs in the Generation I or II game an=
d in Pok=C3=A9mon Bank.
</p>
<h4><span id=3D"Pok.C3.A9mon_GO"></span><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"P=
ok=C3=A9mon_GO">Pok=C3=A9mon GO</span></h4>
<p>Pok=C3=A9mon can be transported from <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulba=
garden.net/wiki/Pok%C3%A9mon_GO" title=3D"Pok=C3=A9mon GO">Pok=C3=A9mon GO<=
/a> to <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Pok%C3%A9mon:_Let=
%27s_Go,_Pikachu!_and_Let%27s_Go,_Eevee!" title=3D"Pok=C3=A9mon: Let's Go, =
Pikachu! and Let's Go, Eevee!">Pok=C3=A9mon: Let's Go, Pikachu! and Let's G=
o, Eevee!</a> at the <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/GO_=
Park" title=3D"GO Park">GO Park complex</a>, or to <a href=3D"https://bulba=
pedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Pok%C3%A9mon_HOME" title=3D"Pok=C3=A9mon HOME">P=
ok=C3=A9mon HOME</a> through the <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.=
net/wiki/GO_Transporter" title=3D"GO Transporter">GO Transporter</a>. Due t=
o these games having a different IV systems, the IVs of transported Pok=C3=
=A9mon must be converted.
</p><p>The Pok=C3=A9mon's HP, Attack, and Defense IVs in the core series ga=
me are its corresponding stats in Pok=C3=A9mon GO, multiplied by 2, plus 1.=
 Its Special Attack IV is always equal to its Attack IV, and its Special De=
fense IV is always equal to its Defense IV. Its Speed IV is randomly genera=
ted upon being caught in the <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/=
wiki/GO_Park" title=3D"GO Park">GO Park complex</a> or transported through =
the <a href=3D"https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/GO_Transporter" titl=
e=3D"GO Transporter">GO Transporter</a>.
</p>
